Diagnosis . MALE. This species is recognized by the deeply excised mandible with the tooth forming an oblique angle (see Pitts et al . 2009 : Fig. 45 ), the lack of mesosternal processes, the marginal cell shorter than the stigma, the first segment of the metasoma petiolate with the second segment, and the genitalia with a short cylindrical cuspis (see Pitts et al . 2009 :
